In the beginning, an "orb" is cast unto Earth. "It" can do two things: change into the form of the thing that stimulates "it"; and come back to life after death. "It" morphs from orb to rock, then to wolf, and finally to boy, but roams about like a newborn who knows nothing. As a boy, "it" becomes Fushi.
Through encounters with human kindness, Fushi not only gains survival skills but grows as a "person". But his journey is darkened by the inexplicable and destructive enemy Nokker and cruel partings with the people he loves.
(Source: Crunchyroll)

Yasuri Shichika, seventh successor of the Kyotouryuu (bladeless) sword art, lives on an isolated island with his older sister, Nanami. One day Shichika is visited by a woman named Togame, who requests his aid in her quest to find and collect the final twelve swords forged by the legendary master swordsmith, Shikizaki Kiki. Shichika and Togame begin their odyssey by leaving the island he called home for over 20 years. They will face twelve individuals who possess and protect Shikizaki's legendary swords. Join Shichika and Togame on an exciting, epic adventure that defies reality as they discover the true potential of the Kyoutoryuu sword style! (Source: NIS America)

Love is always troubling. You want to have the courage to tell someone how you feel. You want to know who he likes. You want someone to listen to your worries. You want someone to give you a push. I know how you feel, and it hurts. Because I had a past I couldn't forget. And because now I have the "power" to save them.... That's why I, Io Akashi, became an angel. "I've finally found you, the angel of Kuze High." The angel touched the girl's cheek, in order to correct Yuzuki Minato's abnormal tendency to fall in love. This is a slightly mysterious coming-of-age story where memory and love play out softly.
(Source: Dengeki Bunko, translated)
Hahaoya ga Ero Ranobe Taishou Jushou Shite Jinsei Tsunda: Semete Musuko no Love Come ni Mazaranai de Kudasai

Life Is A Mess Since My Mom Won An Ero-Novel Grand Prize~ At Least Don’t Mess With Your Son’s Romantic Comedy!
My life is in hard mode because of my mother who loves me so much!
A mother-son incest Ero-Novel written by a mother, Mirei, was somehow able to win the grand prize, but for some reason, her son was the one who attended and received the reward? That’s ridiculous! Ahem! nevermind I mean it’s cliche. Furthermore, a current JK author who also won the award at the same time is also… yesh the MC’s crush.
To explain it further It’s a story about the MC’s life with a son-con mother who’s also an upcoming author for a sensual novel.
